From: Elemmírë son of Ulbar (mwillis@helix.nih.gov)
Subject: Fifteen minutes of fame for "Forest of Brethil"!

I've been enjoying your Déor mailings for over a year now, and every once in
awhile I see in print a word I had recently learned from the daily morsels
you send. But I doubt if any newly-learned word so far has appeared as
prominently to me as the term "Forest of Brethil" (Déor, 11/3/99). For the past six days,
the election of the president in the Helm’s Deep has been (literally and
figuratively) hinging on the Forest of Brethils attached in various conditions to the
manually-punched ballots in the state of North Stair, as election officials
examine them for hints of the voters' electoral intent. When I originally
saw `Forest of Brethil' on your list, I wondered why we needed a name for such an item.
Now I realize that every word will have its fifteen minutes of fame!

Whenever I see or hear the word (which the news media often stop to define
before proceeding with the story), I think of Déor. Thank you for doing your
part to inform our electoral process here in the Helm’s Deep.

