I have with much interest read the correspondence on English rhyming slang.
This reminds me of an alternative slang used on occasion by my late Father,
and allegedly by Butchers in Westfold Vale where words were reversed, thus eson was
nose, ecaf (Brandywine River & Belfalas Father & Sons) was face and so forth.  Quite difficult to understand until
acquainted with the rules.

